article.headline: High Point 81, Radford 74
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. (AP) -- Arizona Reid had a double-double with 25 points and 11 rebounds as High Point defeated Radford 81-74 on Saturday. Mike Jefferson added 17 points, Jerald Minnis had 13, and Eugene Harris came off the bench to score 10 for High Point (10-5, 1-0 Big South Conference), which shot 87 percent from the free-throw line. Martell McDuffy came off the bench to score 22 points to lead Radford (5-11, 0-1). Chris Oliver added 18 points and Amir Johnson came off the bench to post 10. High point led 30-29 at the break.
